    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-11-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1101"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1101">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9709.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to Panama</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your November 10, 2 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d1101fn1">See footnote to the
                        telegram of November 7, 10 p.m.</note> The Government of Panama replies that
                    as the efforts of President Wilson to restore constitutional government in
                    Mexico is generous and noble, the Panaman representative has been instructed to
                    say that Panama sympathizes with those efforts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
